

MALAYA

   pronounced MAH-LAH-YAH

   root word: [66]layà (meaning: freedom, liberty)

   malaya
   free, emancipated

   nakalaya
   was able to become free

   lumaya
   to become free

   pagpapalaya
   liberation

   Malaya is also the name of a national newspaper in the Philippines.

   The Tagalog word for ‘free’ as in ‘no financial cost’ is [67]libre.
